---
description: Website CMS page content conventions
globs: app/[locale]/(system)/website/**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---

# Website Content Source Of Truth

- Treat DB content as the source of truth for page content and image URLs.
- Use `next-intl` only for dashboard UI labels, form labels, button text, and error/success messages.
- For editable page content, read/write via `/api/website/content/:slug`.
- Keep page content locale-aware and pass locale when saving non-bilingual payloads.
- Use fallback-safe rendering: handle missing content gracefully and avoid hardcoded content strings.

# Home Page Convention

- `home` uses bilingual payload saves (`scope=bilingual`) with `ar` and `en` blocks.
- Store hero image URL under `heroSection.backgroundImage`.
